						<summary>

						<p>States that <hi rend="bold">Bollaya-Nāyaka</hi> chief of <hi rend="bold">Maḍapalli</hi> on the southern bank of the Gōdāvarī rebuilt the temple of Bhīmanātha of <hi rend="bold">Piṅgali</hi> and endowed it with land. This was done during the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kākatīya Rudradēva-Mahārāja.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
